        <body>
            <div type="writingSession">
                <opener>
                    <dateline><pb/>
                        <hi rendition="#mPrint">Hull.</hi> 2 July <hi rendition="#mPrint">186</hi>7<hi rendition="#mPrint">.</hi></dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Fred<hi rendition="#sup">k</hi> Engels Esq<hi rendition="#sup">e</hi><lb/>Msrs Ermen &amp; Engels<lb/>Manchester</p>
                <p>Sir</p>
                <p>The Hero sails for <seg type="comment"><orig>Gothenburg</orig><note xml:id="f2f9b276-cf03-4867-afa5-daa668b9b0ae">Göteborg,
                        Schweden.</note></seg>
                    <seg type="comment"><orig>next Saturday</orig><note xml:id="ac0cdd39-617e-47dd-9173-38cec4d2aee3">6. Juli 1867. Zu Engels'
                            Reiseplänen siehe <ref target="B00284"><?oxy_comment_start author="lindenberg" timestamp="20190521T162317+0200" comment="(Br. 275.23–25) und Erl. 275e"?>Engels
                                an Marx, 26.6.1867<?oxy_comment_end?></ref> und Erl.</note></seg>
                    morning at 6 o’clock &amp; you can have a Cabin with 2 berths if you engage one
                    by return for the usual charge viz £ <hi rendition="#u">6.6.0</hi> for 2 berths.
                    The Steamer is laying in <pb/> the Railway dock &amp; will remain there until
                    Saturday morning at 6. &amp; the passage lasts from 44 to 48 hours.</p>
                <closer><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low">Sincere</unclear><lb/>Sir<lb/>Your respectfully<lb/><expan>I<ex>n</ex></expan>
                    <expan>P<ex>erson</ex></expan> T Wilson
                    Sons<lb/>O Theobald <pb/></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
